656. Matuta, or Mater Matuta, was the goddess of dawn: she was confused with Ino who, on throwing herself into the sea, was made a marine goddess and was known thereafter as Leucothea. There was a temple to her in Rome. When Dawn is personified it is usually known as Aurora.
